request that the judge stay the city fine if between now and 
tuesday when the 192000 is due and payable i am satisfied that 
we have reached a point which makes it appropriate that the fines 
be suspended or payments delayed 
the citys fine started at 100 on aug 2 and doubled daily for 
a week until it was stayed pending appeals the city has paid 
12700 so far the fine reaches its 1millionaday cap next 
friday 
gov mario cuomo said he would direct the states emergency 
financial control board on tuesday to begin making the substantial 
reductions in city spending that will be required by sands order 
the board took control of the citys finances aug 9 
even with the cap on the fine yonkers the states 
fourthlargest city with a population of 200000 would be bankrupt 
by midnovember city officials said 
cuomo who had been reluctant to get involved said last week he 
would initiate removal proceedings against the four councilmen if 
the fines were reimposed against the new york suburb 
the control board passed a resolution the same day saying it 
would seek criminal charges against the four if the fines were 
reinstated the allegations would be that the four jeopardized the 
citys fiscal condition violating the law that established the 
control board 
however cuomo spokesman gary fryer said friday that for the 
time being the governor would not attempt to oust the councilmen 
the supreme courts order late thursday stayed a lower court 
ruling that had upheld contempt citations against the four 
councilmen who had been paying their 500aday fines and would 
have been subject to imprisonment this weekend 
on aug 1 the council voted 43 against a desegregation plan 
that would provide incentives to build 800 units of moderateincome 
housing throughout the city sand found the councilmen in contempt 
the next day and since then three additional efforts to pass the 
housing plan have failed 
