mars will move to within about 36 million miles 
of earth this month the closest its been in 17 years and dozens 
of mars watches are planned to view the red planet named for 
the roman god of war 
the planet will come closest to earth on sept 22 but the best 
time to see it is the next few nights said norman warns an 
astronomy professor at south suburban college in south holland a 
chicago suburb 
its a perfect time to see because the moon doesnt come up 
until late at night warns said friday its a definite orange 
bright spot in the southeastern sky at about 10 at night 
