<TEXT>
former prime minister ferit melen died 
saturday of heart trouble the semiofficial anatolia news agency 
reported he was 82 
melen served as finance minister in several governments and was 
named prime minister in 1972 during a succession of above party 
governments after a military takeover resulted in several 
appointments to the turkish cabinet 
in the october 1973 general elections bulent ecevit was elected 
