banned union movement and allowing union pluralism 
but the stakes in the upcoming talks also are high for the 
government after strikes this spring and summer poland appears 
doomed to recurring episodes of costly labor unrest unless the 
government can find a way to build social confidence or at least 
patience for austerity measures to fix the ailing economy 
